      "section_title": "Earthquake",
      "section_content": [
        {
          "sentence": "The tectonics of the northern Philippines and around the island of Luzon are complex",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Luzon is bounded to the east and west by subduction zones",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "In the southern part of Luzon, the subduction zone is located east of the island along the Philippine Trench, where the Philippine Sea Plate subducts westward beneath the Sunda Plate",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "In northern Luzon, where the July 27 earthquake occurred, the subduction zone location and direction changes, with another trench (Manila Trench) located west of Luzon and the Sunda Plate subducts eastward beneath the Philippine Sea Plate",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "The complexity of plate tectonics on and around Luzon is evidenced by the diversity of faulting mechanisms in large earthquakes",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Magnitude 7 or greater earthquakes in this region since 1970 have exhibited reverse, normal, and strike-slip faulting",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "These active plate boundaries lead to high seismic activity",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Since 1970, 11 other earthquakes of magnitude 6.5 or larger have occurred within 250\u00a0km (155\u00a0mi) of the July 27, 2022, earthquake",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "The largest of these earthquakes was a magnitude 7.7 strike-slip earthquake on July 16, 1990, located approximately 215\u00a0km (134\u00a0mi) south of the July 27 earthquake",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "At least 1,600 people died and more than 3,000 people were injured in the 1990 earthquake",
          "refs": []
        },
        {
          "sentence": "The 1990 earthquake also caused landslides, liquefaction, subsidence, and sand boils in the Baguio\u2013Cabanatuan\u2013Dagupan area",
          "refs": []
        }
