              ]
            },
            {
              "sentence": "Despite being a relatively shallow event, no surface ruptures were identified",
              "refs": [
                "https://earthquake.phivolcs.dost.gov.ph/2022_Earthquake_Information/July/2022_0727_0043_B2F.html"
              ]
            },
            {
              "sentence": "A focal mechanism analysis indicate rupture on a reverse fault with either a northeast\u2013southwest striking, steep dipping (69\u00b0) plane or a north\u2013south, shallow dipping (8\u00b0) plane",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "PHIVOLCS initially suspected the earthquake may have occurred on the Abra River Fault",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "Geologists had been aware of the potential for large earthquakes on the fault",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The last known earthquake on the fault was in 1868, measuring 4.0\u20135.0 in magnitude",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The Abra River Fault is a northern extension of the Philippine Fault Zone",
              "refs": [
                "https://mb.com.ph/2022/07/27/abra-river-fault-which-last-moved-in-1868-may-have-triggered-powerful-quake-solidum/"
              ]
            },
            {
              "sentence": "As it runs through Luzon, it splays into three branches that runs beneath the southern Sierra Madre mountains, the Central Cordillera Mountains before terminating at the northern coast of the island",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The three branches strike north-south and are named (west to east) the Vigan-Agao Fault, the Abra River Fault and the Digdig Fault, respectively",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The Philippine Fault Zone is associated with Pliocene and Quaternary uplift of the Cordillera Mountains",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The Abra River and Digdig faults display pure strike-slip displacement, while the Vigan-Agao Fault display a large thrust component",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "In the northern part of Luzon, the Digdig Fault display a normal component",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "However the steep-dipping plane and slip sense associated with the Abra River Fault is not consistent with rupture on it",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The fault which produced the mainshock had a shallow dip angle and produced oblique-reverse displacement",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "A scientific journal published by Rimando and others in 2022 revealed the earthquake did not occur on any of the known faults in the area",
              "refs": [
                "https://temblor.net/earthquake-insights/fault-that-caused-a-july-quake-in-the-philippines-still-in-question-14355/"
